government, state government is fine, state governments can address many of

closer to the problem and can more effectively deal with it.

foreign military bases and cut funding by 90%.  The world should be left to 
its own devices.  Europe should not be protected, the middle east should be 
allowed to remain in chaos, and the U.S should protect itself and no one 
else in the world.

staple of fascism.  Government allows corporatism to happen, with a removal 
of barriers to entry there will be increased competition and a restoration 
of the free market.  There needs to be a removal of economic interests from 
political issues, this is the source of corruption in the U.S.

My grandfather was head of the forest service from '93-96, my father works 
for the government himself.  I oust to be a leftist, but after reading 
Frederick von Hayek, Milton Friedman, John Locke, and George Orwell I 
became a firm libertarian  I'm a economics major, I apply economics to 
these issues and this is the basis of my views.  I'm a firm believer in the 
Austrian school of economics, and the Chicago University school of 
economics.  I formulated my belief system myself with the influence of the 
aforementioned figures.  I am extremely disgruntled, I hate the 
Republicans, I hate the Democrats more.  I am a man without a political 
affiliation, I believe in the free market, liberty, and self reliance.  

Totally agree btw, guns are a tool, people use the tools the wrong way. 
 Gun control is a failed policy, look at Chicago, they have absurd gun 
control and a high murder rate.  Gun violence is a product of poverty, 
poverty created by regulation.  The right to bear arms must be respected 
because guns are needed to overthrow tyrannical governments.  The first 
step to a totalitarian regime is to take away firearms.  

I am not satisfied with the current U.S situation, a number of reforms 
could be made.  It appears I'm never going to make progress, we're both 
firm in our beliefs.  I will say I would rather be left to fend for myself 
then be ruled by government.
